Smugglers' Notch Resort.description:
Smugglers' Notch Resort is famous for providing families with special vacation memories year round in Vermont's beautiful Green Mountains. Winter means skiing and riding on three interconnected mountains on northern Vermont's biggest vertical rise at 2,610 feet and 78 trails offering fun and excitement to all ability levels. Expert instruction for children and adults is provided by the Resort's Snow Sport University in skiing, snowboarding, cross country skiing and snowshoeing. Full-day instruction for children in skiing and snowboarding begins at age 3.
Off the slopes, Winter activities include snow tubing; zip lining through a series of tree platforms on an exciting canopy tour; airboarding; snowmobiling; swimming in the indoor pool and enjoying the hot tub; craft and health and wellness classes; ice skating;
The self-contained condominium Village offers slopeside accommodations ranging in size from studios to five bedroom townhouses as well as services including a convenience grocery store, restaurants, sport shop, and equipment rental and repair shop. Smugglers' commitment to service and a Family Fun Guarantee make it America's Family Resort. Smugglers' is located 35 miles east of Burlington.
